Unit support. I wonder if reflection on class annotations in the native image will work if the annotation classes are retained. It seems the native image could strip metadata unless those annotations are explicitly registered. I need to think through how this all ties together and if that affects our test executions effectively.\\n\\n**Identifying potential issues**\\n\\nI'm noticing some potential compile issues related to the `default @DiscriminatorMapping`. It seems to be missing parens in the source, which might be an annotation type issue. There’s also a concern regarding the `Content` field having `@Target({ ElementType.FIELD })` but being used nested. Then, `ExternalDocumentation` targets FIELD but appears as default in Operation, which feels a bit strange. However, I see no problem with the required title and version for `@Info`.\\n\\n**Checking code imports**\\n\\nI'm thinking that there might be some old packages in the user-code-filter, but I notice there are no test imports mentioned. It seems like the final mention hasn’t run. I should probably check for any differences in the code by looking at `git diff`. This will help me ensure everything is up to date and running smoothly!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0e4fa27c970806100169f87c71e94481a29f9a82de9393893c\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-HyF9bwnD0Fgnm9tEPf67nVYlguAleQn84XW2Ag4tRrFqgFiEa2KopShlEBao3k1hyRmB4w75CFt3f8unqLXyOSRszAyBla3ZPal1fBKh-0MtVmmPVWHPSCF1BsBwXHEyVQ35ZL5CpQ2xPlinCXCgNdmpRjcZzXDvWJO5tU4mAM4lZGW-wBbsG1gjCaHinnftg4P--YtFRRq8-9cSG8vIOAT5g7Zjd2vuvj2JkSNDJuUOwkFZhrSiLTn8H3d3ktELB66ITuS921NsCLzxlaWxykVu03AWmGBzg63UIaNEzVpj7Kfnor-1Aa7HYZ9JG9yfj9HCcNyenLeH8DdSiFM1plxEnnEGuFgVIJnNHv2YnJxUm92nqkelQ1aebxxD6s2C3IdFTk6_4UP3njgESzqUQINdpX7QB4WMX-Ld6KvdOask0Zqfqhov2jSASgIcLTLoZ2plgXYI8etS1UNP-ls0Kv5J2oBFMAmqUJw0HafUIjPcFoM496670HwFLQCBaHcteRla4jcPKwy1X-2rwUBqidEDym4uQ_G3w4sCI5de8PuDiCubDc8yN5w3OQdh9DMrZKI5zQlzK5UfnucOqiytVelIorZhojeanY2pNocE2C