*Examining Gradle issues**\\\\n\\\\nI'm noticing a potential issue with opening only the source files related to classes listed in the Gradle error output. We've opened some sources not in the output but related to the new ApiResponse. Another point is about stopping source inspections; I wonder if we need to update the user-code filter? If the Native run fails, it might be due to missing metadata for the new package.   \\\\n\\\\nTests are compiled in TCK with a metadata repository, but it seems like there’s only metadata for version 1.6.2. I need to figure out if metadata is essential for annotations or if it's included in the Native Image. It seems annotations need metadata for runtime visibility; maybe we need to register methods or fields for that? Existing tests might have only generated metadata for the library.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Exploring TCK harness and annotations**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering that the TCK harness might register test classes reflectively, and typically, native tests use JUnit support. I wonder if reflection on class annotations in the native image will work if the annotation classes are retained. It seems the native image could strip metadata unless those annotations are explicitly registered. I need to think through how this all ties together and if that affects our test executions effectively.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Identifying potential issues**\\\\n\\\\nI'm noticing some potential compile issues related to the `default @DiscriminatorMapping`. It seems to be missing parens in the source, which might be an annotation type issue. There’s also a concern regarding the `Content` field having `@Target({ ElementType.FIELD })` but being used nested. Then, `ExternalDocumentation` targets FIELD but appears as default in Operation, which feels a bit strange. However, I see no problem with the required title and version for `@Info`.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Checking code imports**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking that there might be some old packages in the user-code-filter, but I notice there are no test imports mentioned. It seems like the final mention hasn’t run. I should probably check for any differences in the code by looking at `git diff`. This will help me ensure everything is up to date and running smoothly!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_HmUZWdjbxu6sw7hWD2hwaTjv|fc_0e4fa27c970806100169f87c8543a481a2a3d34d92691443ba\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"git diff -- tests/src/io.swagger/swagger-annotations/2.0.0-rc0/src/test/java/io_swagger/swagger_annotations/Swagger_annotationsTest.java | sed -n '1,220p'\", \"timeout\": 60}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 387, \"output\": 1136, \"cacheRead\": 57856, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 59379, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777892461995, \"responseId\": \"resp_0e4fa27c970806100169f87c6e962481a29ee90290ae007611\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_HmUZWdjbxu6sw7hWD2hwaTjv|fc_0e4fa27c970806100169f87c8543a481a2a3d34d92691443ba\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"diff --git i/tests/src/io.swagger/swagger-annotations/2.0.0-rc0/src/test/java/io_swagger/swagger_annotations/Swagger_annotationsTest.java w/tests/src/io.swagger/swagger-annotations/2.0.0-rc0/src/test/java/io_swagger/swagger_annotations/Swagger_annotationsTest.java\\nindex 87c90ff404..aa8cc41f56 100644\\n--- i/tests/src/io.swagger/swagger-annotations/2.0.0-rc0/src/test/java/io_swagger/swagger_annotations/Swagger_annotationsTest.java\\n+++ w/tests/src/io.swagger/swagger-annotations/2.0.0-rc0/src/test/java/io_swagger/swagger_annotations/Swagger_annotationsTest.java\\n@@ -6,33 +6,31 @@\\n  */\\n package io_swagger.swagger_